<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-03T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-03T21:00:00-05:00" n="55" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/23406:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Afghanistan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-03T22:00:00-04:00">September
                                    3, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>36. While demands elsewhere and other considerations render improbable
                            adoption of the proposal contained in your 49 of August 7, 10 p.m., the
                            matter is under consideration and if a decision is reached in accordance
                            with your recommendation you will be notified immediately.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>